<font color="#FF0000">FALSE NEWSPAPER REPORTS</font><br>
<tt>Fri Feb 13 16:47:59 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
Thank you for the copy of the article.  It is a shining example of the quality of reporting by the American press concerning the Vietnam War and its veterans.  The aircraft were not jets but rather propeller-driven Skyraiders flown by the South Vietnam Air Force.  Since the picture was first published, the press has been blaming the Americans and South Vietnamese for the tragedy rather than putting the blame where it belongs.  In both the Korean and Vietnam Wars, the communists used the tactic of hiding behind civilians or using them as human shields.  In this way, the Americans, Koreans, or Vietnamese could choose between letting the communist soldiers get close enough to kill them or opening fire and killing innocent civilians.<br><br>
Why did Plummer claim to have directed the strike?  There is a one-word answer: publicity.  He even appeared on German television, where he was even described as the pilot who flew the aircraft.<br><br>
John Plummer has become an international figure and reportedly admitted receiving more attention than he had ever received for all of the sermons combined.  If he decided to run for public office, he would probably win.
